@page "/about"
@using ServiceStack.Mvc
@attribute [RenderStatic]
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "CV";
    ViewData["Description"] = "Magnus Källman — Senior Software Engineer & Cloud Architect";
    ViewData["CanonicalUrl"] = "https://www.sourceman.se/about/";
    Layout = "_Layout";
}

<div class="about-page content-narrow">

    <div class="cv-header">
        <h1 class="cv-name">Magnus Källman</h1>
        <p class="cv-title">Senior Software Engineer · Cloud Architect · Stockholm</p>
    </div>

    <div class="cv-now">
        <div class="cv-now-label">Now</div>
        <p>Engaged at Recharge — building AI agents and agentic workflows to add real business value via Sourceman AB.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="cv-section">
        <h2 class="about-heading">Experience</h2>
        <p class="cv-section-intro">I take pride in my craft, and the quality of the software I ship matters deeply to me.</p>
        <p class="cv-section-intro">I have been coding since 2006 and started out as a professional web developer in the age of jQuery and Internet Explorer, with .NET Framework on the server.</p>
        <p class="cv-section-intro">For the past ten years, my focus has been backend engineering — writing scalable, maintainable and performant applications, reaching for the techniques that fit each specific problem.</p>
        <p class="cv-section-intro">Since the early period of my career I have been taking responsibility for build and deployment infrastructure, and have shipped pipelines on TeamCity, Octopus Deploy, Azure DevOps, and GitHub Actions.</p>
        <p class="cv-section-intro">In my spare time, I've tinkered with everything from compilers, machine learning and IoT to cloud and web development.</p>
        <p class="cv-section-intro">Below is a selection of my longer-running consultancy engagements. I tend to stay with the same clients for extended periods, learning the business and compounding value over time — though I've also done short, targeted work, such as introducing better developer tooling and workflows or helping teams survive Black Friday traffic peaks.</p>
        <blockquote class="about-quote">
            Software performance <em>is still</em> one of the most overlooked features.
        </blockquote>
        <div class="cv-entries">

            <div class="cv-entry">
                <div>
                    <div class="cv-entry-company">Recharge</div>
                    <div class="cv-entry-role">AI Engineer</div>
                    <p class="cv-entry-desc">Building AI agents and agentic workflows that deliver measurable business value for enterprise clients.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="cv-entry-dates">Jan 2026 – Present</div>
            </div>

            <div class="cv-entry">
                <div>
                    <div class="cv-entry-company">Martin &amp; Servera</div>
                    <div class="cv-entry-role">Solution Architect/Senior Backend Engineer</div>
                    <p class="cv-entry-desc">Led backend API development for mobile application. Built microservice architecture on Azure with .NET, Docker, and async patterns.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="cv-entry-dates">Mar 2023 – Mar 2026</div>
            </div>

            <div class="cv-entry">
                <div>
                    <div class="cv-entry-company">Afound</div>
                    <div class="cv-entry-role">Episerver Architect</div>
                    <p class="cv-entry-desc">Took ownership of a large legacy e-commerce codebase. Drove modernization of development practices and tooling across the team and expansion to multiple markets.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="cv-entry-dates">Feb 2019 – Jun 2022</div>
            </div>

            <div class="cv-entry">
                <div>
                    <div class="cv-entry-company">Natur &amp; Kultur</div>
                    <div class="cv-entry-role">Solution Architect · Lead Developer</div>
                    <p class="cv-entry-desc">Rebuilt the publisher's website on the latest Episerver Commerce stack with continuous delivery from day one.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="cv-entry-dates">Dec 2017 – Aug 2018</div>
            </div>

            <div class="cv-entry">
                <div>
                    <div class="cv-entry-company">Type &amp; Tell</div>
                    <div class="cv-entry-role">Solution Architect</div>
                    <p class="cv-entry-desc">Designed and built a self-publishing platform — professional book creation tools for independent authors.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="cv-entry-dates">Jan 2015 – Dec 2017</div>
            </div>

            <div class="cv-entry">
                <div>
                    <div class="cv-entry-company">Coop</div>
                    <div class="cv-entry-role">Developer</div>
                    <p class="cv-entry-desc">Developer on coop.se — one of Sweden's largest food retail websites.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="cv-entry-dates">Aug 2012 – Dec 2014</div>
            </div>

        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="cv-section">
        <h2 class="about-heading">Skills</h2>
        <div class="cv-skills">
            <span class="cv-skill-tag">Microsoft Azure</span>
            <span class="cv-skill-tag">.NET</span>
            <span class="cv-skill-tag">Go</span>
            <span class="cv-skill-tag">Rust</span>
            <span class="cv-skill-tag">Cloud Architecture</span>
            <span class="cv-skill-tag">CI/CD</span>
            <span class="cv-skill-tag">Microservices</span>
            <span class="cv-skill-tag">Event-Driven Architecture</span>
            <span class="cv-skill-tag">Docker</span>
            <span class="cv-skill-tag">Multi-Tier Caching</span>
            <span class="cv-skill-tag">Redis</span>
            <span class="cv-skill-tag">AI Agents</span>
            <span class="cv-skill-tag">Performance Engineering</span>
            <span class="cv-skill-tag">Advanced Troubleshooting</span>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="cv-section">
        <h2 class="about-heading">Certifications</h2>
        <p class="cv-section-intro">While i don't cherish certificates and the act of taken the exams, learning is both immensely fun and important. Here are some certificates i've acquired in the past.</p>
        <ul class="cv-cert-list">
            <li><span>Certified Scrum Master — Scrum Alliance</span><span class="cv-cert-year">2017</span></li>
            <li><span>MCSD: Web Applications — Microsoft</span><span class="cv-cert-year">2013</span></li>
            <li><span>EPiServer Certified Developer</span><span class="cv-cert-year">2012</span></li>
            <li><span>MCTS: .NET Framework 4, Web Applications</span><span class="cv-cert-year">2012</span></li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <section class="about-links cv-section">
        <h2 class="about-heading">Find me</h2>
        <ul class="link-list">
            <li>
                <a href="https://github.com/magkal" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub</a>
                <span class="link-handle">@@magkal</span>
            </li>
            <li>
                <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/magnus-k%C3%A4llman-976167114/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">LinkedIn</a>
                <span class="link-handle">Magnus Källman</span>
            </li>
        </ul>
    </section>

</div>
